## Description {#details}

<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/pdb/pdbsymbol">PDBSymbol</a> defines the base of the inheritance hierarchy for concrete symbol types (e.g.

functions, executables, vtables, etc). All concrete symbol types inherit from <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/pdb/pdbsymbol">PDBSymbol</a> and expose the exact set of methods that are valid for that particular symbol type, as described in the Microsoft reference &quot;Lexical and Class Hierarchy of Symbol Types&quot;: <a href="https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/370hs6k4.aspx">https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/370hs6k4.aspx</a>

Definition at line 71 of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/debuginfo/include/llvm/debuginfo/pdb/pdbsymbol-h">PDBSymbol.h</a>.

### dump() {#a97c3bdbd0e05f8c6815424229f4b3d1c}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>virtual void llvm::pdb::PDBSymbol::dump (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/pdb/pdbsymdumper">PDBSymDumper</a> &amp; Dumper) const</>}>
Dumps the contents of a symbol a <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/raw-ostream">raw&#95;ostream</a>.

By default this will just call <a href="#a97c3bdbd0e05f8c6815424229f4b3d1c">dump()</a> on the underlying RawSymbol, which allows us to discover unknown properties, but individual implementations of <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/pdb/pdbsymbol">PDBSymbol</a> may override the behavior to only dump known fields.
